results.name: a(n) = the smallest composite positive integer that is not yet in the sequence and that is coprime to n.
comment: This sequence is a permutation of the composite positive integers.
Each composite k occurs in the sequence no later than a(k-1). Proof by induction. - _Peter Munn_, Sep 01 2017
link: Michael De Vlieger, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..3000
mathematica: a = {4}; Do[k = 6; While[Nand[CompositeQ@ k, ! MemberQ[a, k], CoprimeQ[k, n]], k++]; AppendTo[a, k], {n, 2, 69}]; a (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Jul 23 2017 *)
